Privacy Policy
Effective Date: 04 September 2024

1. Introduction
Welcome to AHFoZ Conference App. Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy outlines how we handle any information when you use our app, which provides information about events, programs, facilitators, and sponsors.

2. No Information Collection
Our app does not collect, store, or process any personal or non-personal information. We do not require you to create an account or provide any data while using our app.

3. No Third-Party Services
Our app does not include or interact with any third-party services. We do not share any information with external parties.

4. Data Security
Since we do not collect any information, there are no data security measures necessary related to user data. However, we still implement general security practices to ensure the app's proper functioning.

5. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected by updating the effective date at the top of this policy. We encourage you to review this policy periodically.

6. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

Email: samuelmakoh@gmail.com

7. Consent
By using our app, you acknowledge and consent to the terms outlined in this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with this policy, please refrain from using our app.
